---
title: Melty Monterey Jack Burgers with Red Onion Jam, Garlic Mayo & Crispy Potato Wedges
description: There are a lot of burger recipes out there, we know. But we like to think that this is the burger that tops all burgers, thanks to oozy, melty Monterey Jack cheese and jammy balsamic onions. Oh, and we should mention that this patty comes with seasoned oven fries on the side, because how could we not?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/melty-monterey-jack-burgers-bfe0a19b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/melty-monterey-jack-burgers-5e25f552b9721f76446c7585-b5190a10.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 990 kcal
  fat: 53 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 900 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/melty-monterey-jack-burgers-5e25f552b9721f76446c7585
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.
Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} (2 cloves for 4 servings). Halve, peel, and
thinly slice @red onion{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp},
half the @fry seasoning{1%tbsp} (all the seasoning for 4 servings),
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and
softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} and
@sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings). Continue cooking until caramelized and
jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.
Transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

In a second small bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and a pinch of
@garlic{1%clove}(minced) (taste and add more from there if desired). Season
with salt and pepper.

Shape @ground beef{10%ounce} into two equal-sized patties (four patties for
4 servings); season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{} in pan used to cook onion over medium-high heat. Add patties
and cook almost to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Top each patty
with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/2%cup}. Cover pan to melt cheese and allow
patties to finish cooking, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Halve @potato buns{2} and toast until golden. Spread toasted buns with
@ketchup{2%tbsp} and garlic mayo to taste. Fill with patties and as much
onion jam as you like. Serve with potatoes on the side.

> TIP: If onion starts to brown too quickly, add a splash of water when
cooking the onion.

> There are a lot of burger recipes out there, we know. But we like to think
that this is the burger that tops all burgers, thanks to oozy, melty
Monterey Jack cheese and jammy balsamic onions. Oh, and we should mention
that this patty comes with seasoned oven fries on the side, because how
could we not?